## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

This is documentation for MongoDB Managed Service for Pivotal Cloud Foundry.
The MongoDB Managed Service enables Cloud FoundryÂ® users to provision MongoDB databases in a variety of configurations, from standalone instances to replicated, sharded clusters. Binding applications to a MongoDB service instance provides a unique credential to connect with and manage a MongoDB database on the deployed set / cluster. This tile requires a licensed copy of MongoDB Ops Manager.

Key Features

* The ability to provision a MongoDB service instance in standalone, replica set or sharded cluster configuration.
* Binding applications to the instance creates unique credentials for each application to access the database.
* Supports deployment of MongoDB Community or Enterprise server.


